### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

### Créer un premier customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "firstName": "Jean",
  "lastName": "Dupont",
  "email": "jean.dupont@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "0123456789",
  "address": "123 Rue de la Paix",
  "city": "Paris",
  "postalCode": "75001",
  "country": "France"
}

### Créer un deuxième customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "firstName": "Marie",
  "lastName": "Martin",
  "email": "marie.martin@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "0987654321",
  "address": "456 Avenue des Champs",
  "city": "Lyon",
  "postalCode": "69000",
  "country": "France"
}

### Créer un troisième customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "firstName": "Pierre",
  "lastName": "Bernard",
  "email": "pierre.bernard@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "0612345678",
  "address": "789 Boulevard Saint-Germain",
  "city": "Bordeaux",
  "postalCode": "33000",
  "country": "France"
}

### Récupérer tous les customers
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Récupérer un customer par ID (ID=1)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/1
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Récupérer un customer par ID (ID=2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/2
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Récupérer un customer par email
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/email/jean.dupont@example.com
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Récupérer un customer par email - Marie
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/email/marie.martin@example.com
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Récupérer un customer qui n'existe pas (erreur 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/999
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Mettre à jour un customer (ID=1)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "firstName": "Jean-Claude",
  "lastName": "Dupont",
  "email": "jean-claude.dupont@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "0133333333",
  "address": "123 Rue de la Paix Apt 4",
  "city": "Paris",
  "postalCode": "75002",
  "country": "France"
}

### Mettre à jour un customer (ID=2)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/2
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "firstName": "Marie-Sophie",
  "lastName": "Martin",
  "email": "marie-sophie.martin@example.com",
  "phoneNumber": "0987654322",
  "address": "456 Avenue des Champs Etage 2",
  "city": "Lyon",
  "postalCode": "69001",
  "country": "France"
}

### Mettre à jour un customer qui n'existe pas (erreur 404)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/999
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "firstName": "Inexistant",
  "lastName": "Client",
  "email": "inexistant@example.com"
}

### Supprimer un customer (ID=3)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/3

### Vérifier que le customer a bien été supprimé (erreur 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/3
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Supprimer un customer qui n'existe pas (erreur 404)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/999

### Récupérer tous les customers (après modifications)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/customers
Accept: {{contentType}}

